Class Vector.Vector0

java.lang.Object
civitas.celestis.math.vector.Vector.Vector0
All Implemented Interfaces:
Vector<Vector.Vector0>, Serializable
Enclosing interface:
Vector<V extends Vector<V>>
public static final class Vector.Vector0 extends Object implements Vector<Vector.Vector0>
A zero-dimensional vector. The non-existent component value is presumed to be zero, and arithmetic logic is implemented accordingly.

      public boolean equals(@Nullable Object obj)
      Checks for equality between this vector and the provided object obj. This will check if the other object is also a vector, and that the dimension count, composition, and order of components are all equal. In other words, this checks if the other object is also a vector of the same numerical value.
